Rowland, MG Ryan, S Sitch, Martijn Slot, NG Smith, MH Turnbull , MC VanderWel, F Valladares, EJ Veneklaas, LK Weerasinghe, C Wirth, IJ Wright, K Wythers, J Xiang, S Xiang, and J Zaragoza-Castells (2015) Global variability in leaf respiration among plant functional types in relation to climate and leaf traits. Comment: Leaf  mass per unit leaf area

Dataset: Northern mixed-grass prairie species traits - Wyoming, USA
TraitName: Leaf area per leaf dry mass (specific leaf area, SLA or 1/LMA): petiole included
Reference: unpub.
Comment: mean single leaf area for each sampled plant, petioles and rachis included, Special cases: (1) Artemisia frigida; Phlox hoodii--these species have very small leaflets arranged in bunches. We selected a representative leaf bunch from each sampled plant and separated all leaflets for leaf mass and area measurements (thus, leaf number varies among replicate samples); (2) Allium textile--this species had thick, roughly cylindrical leaves. We corrected the projected one-sided leaf area by the ratio of leaf circumference to width to obtain a more accurate leaf area.
